    "body": "<!--\r\n  Thank you for contributing to Neovim!\r\n  If this is your first time, check out https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md#pull-requests-prs\r\n  for our PR guidelines.\r\n-->\r\n\r\n## Problem\r\nExpanding a snippet while another snippet is active overwrites the current\r\nsession, leaving no way to return to the outer snippet.\r\n\r\n## Solution\r\nKeep a session stack. On `expand()`, push the current session; on `stop()`,\r\npop and restore the previous session (and clean up extmarks/autocmds).\r\n\r\n--- \r\n\r\nWe also have https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/29340, but it hasn't been updated since June 2024.\r\n\r\nclose #29340",
    "closed_at": "2026-04-08T21:34:46Z",
    "comment_data": [],
    "comment_regular_data": [
